Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 3cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. 

> Tip: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf for ~{20%minutes} - you'll roast them for longer once you've crushed them.

Meanwhile, cut the @tomato{2%medium}(cut into 2cm pieces).

Add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing to a large #bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper, then mix well. Stir the tomatoes into the dressing, then set aside.

Trim and halve the @green beans{150%g}. Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, separate the leaves, then tear into bite-sized pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.

Once cooked, transfer the lardons to a small #bowl{} and set aside the pan, keeping the bacon fat.

When the potatoes have cooked for 20 mins, remove them from the oven.

Use the bottom of a #bowl{} or pan to lightly crush each potato.

Drizzle the smashed potatoes with more @olive oil{1%tbsp}, and return to the top shelf of your oven until crispy and golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop your frying pan back on medium-high heat, no need to clean.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn the heat down to medium, then add a splash of @water{} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once cooked, add the beans to the tomato bowl along with the @fresh pesto{50%g} and @mayonnaise{64%g}. Gently mix together until everything is combined.

Once the potatoes are cooked, remove them from the oven.

Add the lettuce and smashed potatoes to the bowl of dressed veg and toss to coat.

Share the salad between your bowls and sprinkle over the crispy lardons to finish.

Enjoy!